    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="772"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d772">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.0090/2109a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-31">August 31,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2129. American interests—Japan. Your 5303 August 7 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >27</hi>].<note n="14" xml:id="d772fn14">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1001">p. 1001</ref>.</note>
                    Request Swiss Minister Tokyo inform Japanese authorities that this Government
                    has taken note of these requirements but that it has received the information
                    too late to inform persons addressing mail to internees and prisoners of war for
                    despatch on the <hi rend="italic">Gripsholm</hi>. American Government intends to
                    deliver after censorship mail received on the return voyage of the <hi
                        rend="italic">Gripsholm</hi> addressed to Japanese civilian internees and
                    prisoners of war in this country without placing any limitation on number or
                    length of letters. Since the mail being despatched on the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Gripsholm</hi> has been prepared and is being despatched in good faith the
                    Government of the United States requests the Japanese Government reciprocally to
                    deliver this mail as the American Government will deliver the Japanese mail
                    received.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
